      • IncidentsManager.IncidentRadiusOptions

        public IncidentsManager.IncidentRadiusOptions(GeoPoint center,
                                      double radius)
        Initializes a new instance of the IncidentsManager.IncidentRadiusOptions class.

        The units for the radius is either meters or miles depending on what is set in setUnits(com.inrix.sdk.utils.UserPreferences.Unit). The default units are set using UserPreferences.

        Parameters:
        center - The center of the circular region from which to get the incidents.
        radius - The radius of the circular region.

        public final IncidentsManager.IncidentRadiusOptions setIncidentType(int type)
        Sets the type of incidents to be returned. The default is "ALL" (see IncidentsManager.INCIDENT_RESULT_TYPE_ALL). Multiple types can be specified by using the "or" operator.
        Parameters:
        type - One or more incident types.
        Returns:
        This instance of the IncidentOptions class.

      • setIncidentSource

        public final IncidentsManager.IncidentRadiusOptions setIncidentSource(int incidentSource)
        Sets the requested source of the incidents.

        A value of IncidentsManager.INCIDENT_SOURCE_INRIXONLY specifies that incidents are compiled from non-commercial sources, such as flow incidents that are generated programmatically from Inrix traffic information or planned construction incidents. A value of IncidentsManager.INCIDENT_SOURCE_COMMUNITY specifies that incidents come from community sources, such as incidents submitted through mobile devices. The default is IncidentsManager.INCIDENT_SOURCE_ALL. *

        Parameters:
        incidentSource - The source of the incident information.
        Returns:
        This instance of the IncidentOptions class.

      • setSeverity

        public final IncidentsManager.IncidentRadiusOptions setSeverity(java.lang.Integer[] severity)
        Filters incident reports based on severity level. This value can be in the range of IncidentsManager.INCIDENT_SEVERITY_0- IncidentsManager.INCIDENT_SEVERITY_4, with IncidentsManager.INCIDENT_SEVERITY_4 indicating the highest severity. Multiple severity values can be specified. All severities are returned by default.
        Parameters:
        severity - The set of incident severities.
        Returns:
        This instance of the IncidentOptions class.

      • setRadius

        public final IncidentsManager.IncidentRadiusOptions setRadius(double radius)
        Sets the radius of the circular bounding area from which to return data. Any features that are fully or partially enclosed within the bounding area are selected.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
